verses.text_plain: O give thanks unto the Lord; for he is good: because his mercy endureth for ever.
verses.verse_html: 1O give thanks unto the Lord; for he is good: because his mercy endureth for ever.

verses.text_plain: Let Israel now say, that his mercy endureth for ever.
verses.verse_html: 2Let Israel now say, that his mercy endureth for ever.

verses.text_plain: Let the house of Aaron now say, that his mercy endureth for ever.
verses.verse_html: 3Let the house of Aaron now say, that his mercy endureth for ever.

verses.text_plain: Let them now that fear the Lord say, that his mercy endureth for ever.
verses.verse_html: 4Let them now that fear the Lord say, that his mercy endureth for ever.

verses.text_plain: I called upon the Lord in distress: the Lord answered me, and set me in a large place.
verses.verse_html:
5I called upon the Lord in distress: the Lord answered me, and set me in a large place. ▼
▼ in distress: Heb. out of distress

footnotes.body_text: ▼ in distress: Heb. out of distress
footnotes.body_html: ▼ in distress: Heb. out of distress

verses.text_plain: The Lord is on my side; I will not fear: what can man do unto me?
verses.verse_html:
6The Lord is on my side; I will not fear: what can man do unto me? ▼
▼ on…: Heb. for me

tokens.text: on my side; I will not fear

footnotes.body_html: ▼ on…: Heb. for me

verses.text_plain: The Lord taketh my part with them that help me: therefore shall I see my desire upon them that hate me.
verses.verse_html: 7The Lord taketh my part with them that help me: therefore shall I see my desire upon them that hate me.

tokens.text: taketh my part with them that help

verses.text_plain: It is better to trust in the Lord than to put confidence in man.
verses.verse_html: 8It is better to trust in the Lord than to put confidence in man.

verses.text_plain: It is better to trust in the Lord than to put confidence in princes.
verses.verse_html: 9It is better to trust in the Lord than to put confidence in princes.

verses.text_plain: All nations compassed me about: but in the name of the Lord will I destroy them.
verses.verse_html:
10All nations compassed me about: but in the name of the Lord will I destroy them. ▼
▼ destroy…: Heb. cut them off

footnotes.body_html: ▼ destroy…: Heb. cut them off

verses.text_plain: They compassed me about; yea, they compassed me about: but in the name of the Lord I will destroy them.
verses.verse_html: 11They compassed me about; yea, they compassed me about: but in the name of the Lord I will destroy them.

verses.text_plain: They compassed me about like bees; they are quenched as the fire of thorns: for in the name of the Lord I will destroy them.
verses.verse_html:
12They compassed me about like bees; they are quenched as the fire of thorns: for in the name of the Lord I will destroy them. ▼
▼ destroy: Heb. cut down

footnotes.body_html: ▼ destroy: Heb. cut down

verses.text_plain: Thou hast thrust sore at me that I might fall: but the Lord helped me.
verses.verse_html: 13Thou hast thrust sore at me that I might fall: but the Lord helped me.

tokens.text: at me that I might fall

verses.text_plain: The Lord is my strength and song, and is become my salvation.
verses.verse_html: 14The Lord is my strength and song, and is become my salvation.

verses.text_plain: The voice of rejoicing and salvation is in the tabernacles of the righteous: the right hand of the Lord doeth valiantly.
verses.verse_html: 15The voice of rejoicing and salvation is in the tabernacles of the righteous: the right hand of the Lord doeth valiantly.

verses.text_plain: The right hand of the Lord is exalted: the right hand of the Lord doeth valiantly.
verses.verse_html: 16The right hand of the Lord is exalted: the right hand of the Lord doeth valiantly.

verses.text_plain: I shall not die, but live, and declare the works of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 17I shall not die, but live, and declare the works of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: The Lord hath chastened me sore: but he hath not given me over unto death.
verses.verse_html: 18The Lord hath chastened me sore: but he hath not given me over unto death.

tokens.text: but he hath not given me over

verses.text_plain: Open to me the gates of righteousness: I will go into them, and I will praise the Lord:
verses.verse_html: 19Open to me the gates of righteousness: I will go into them, and I will praise the Lord:

verses.text_plain: This gate of the Lord, into which the righteous shall enter.
verses.verse_html: 20This gate of the Lord, into which the righteous shall enter.

verses.text_plain: I will praise thee: for thou hast heard me, and art become my salvation.
verses.verse_html: 21I will praise thee: for thou hast heard me, and art become my salvation.

tokens.text: me, and art become my salvation

verses.text_plain: The stone which the builders refused is become the head stone of the corner.
verses.verse_html: 22The stone which the builders refused is become the head stone of the corner.

verses.text_plain: This is the Lord’s doing; it is marvellous in our eyes.
verses.verse_html:
23This is the Lord’s doing; it is marvellous in our eyes. ▼
▼ the Lord’s…: Heb. from the Lord

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the Lord’s…: Heb. from the Lord
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the Lord’s…: Heb. from the Lord

verses.text_plain: This is the day which the Lord hath made; we will rejoice and be glad in it.
verses.verse_html: 24This is the day which the Lord hath made; we will rejoice and be glad in it.

verses.text_plain: Save now, I beseech thee, O Lord: O Lord, I beseech thee, send now prosperity.
verses.verse_html: 25Save now, I beseech thee, O Lord: O Lord, I beseech thee, send now prosperity.

verses.text_plain: Blessed be he that cometh in the name of the Lord: we have blessed you out of the house of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 26Blessed be he that cometh in the name of the Lord: we have blessed you out of the house of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: God is the Lord, which hath shewed us light: bind the sacrifice with cords, even unto the horns of the altar.
verses.verse_html: 27God is the Lord, which hath shewed us light: bind the sacrifice with cords, even unto the horns of the altar.

verses.text_plain: Thou art my God, and I will praise thee: thou art my God, I will exalt thee.
verses.verse_html: 28Thou art my God, and I will praise thee: thou art my God, I will exalt thee.

verses.text_plain: O give thanks unto the Lord; for he is good: for his mercy endureth for ever.
verses.verse_html: 29O give thanks unto the Lord; for he is good: for his mercy endureth for ever.
